about.summary: Set of tools for reading and processing spatial data. The aim is to supply the workflow to create thematic maps. This package also facilitates 'tmap', the package for visualizing thematic maps.

name: r-tmaptools
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '2.0-1' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-tmaptools
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/tmaptools_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/tmaptools/tmaptools_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 9febf4dc5128ddc977bdecfb0c3dd32e99f280b0aec5787f3fab76720716d27d

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-kernsmooth
    - r-rcolorbrewer
    - r-xml
    - r-classint
    - r-dichromat
    - r-lwgeom >=0.1_4
    - r-magrittr
    - r-raster >=2.5_2
    - r-rgdal
    - r-rgeos
    - r-sf >=0.6_0
    - r-sp
    - r-units >=0.5_1
    - r-viridislite
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-kernsmooth
    - r-rcolorbrewer
    - r-xml
    - r-classint
    - r-dichromat
    - r-lwgeom >=0.1_4
    - r-magrittr
    - r-raster >=2.5_2
    - r-rgdal
    - r-rgeos
    - r-sf >=0.6_0
    - r-sp
    - r-units >=0.5_1
    - r-viridislite

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('tmaptools')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('tmaptools')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/mtennekes/tmaptools
  license: GPL-3
  summary: Set of tools for reading and processing spatial data. The aim is to supply the workflow
    to create thematic maps. This package also facilitates 'tmap', the package for visualizing
    thematic maps.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'
  doc_url: https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/tmaptools/tmaptools.pdf
  dev_url: https://github.com/mtennekes/tmaptools

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - agcopenhaver
